Slovak Inflation Rate Rises to 4% in May, a 29-Month High

-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k
-- 
2011-06-13T07:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/slovak-inflation-rate-rises-to-4-in-may-a-29-month-high.html
Slovakia’s inflation rate rose to 4
percent in May, the highest since December 2008, from 3.7
percent in the previous month, the nation’s statistics office
said today in Bratislava.  On a monthly basis, consumer prices advanced 0.3 percent in
May, compared with a 0.4 percent increase in the previous month.
Rising the most were prices of shoes and clothing, which were up
1.2 percent, followed by a 1 percent increase in food prices.  To contact the reporter on this story:
